<br>
Christians pick and choose out of the Bible.&quot;<br>
<br>
The old Mosaic law applied to the Ancient Israelites for whom it was written.  Its role in the modern day Bible is as history, like all the rest of the material in the books surrounding it.  This is a very basic and easily grasped concept.  Christians do not live by the Mosaic law because its function is to teach us what God's will for the ancient Israelites was, and for us to learn from it.  We have an updated version, so to speak, in the New Testament that, while it does not invalidate the Old Testament, supercedes it... that is why Christians do not offer burnt offerings like Israelites do to this day, even though it is written in the Old Testament as a very definite command.  So you ask, how do you know which is which?  Most of us don't, and that is why it is critical to have an insightful, intelligent pastor/teacher who can make the call.  Of course, each person will have their own individual interpretation, it has always been so in the history of all religions, but my explanation is the generally accepted one.  Feel better now, Boinshar?<br>
<br>
Of course people, being imperfect, are going to obey parts of the Bible and not others.  People will pick and choose those passages they prefer and ignore those that they don't - case in point -  many &quot;Gay Christians&quot;.  Many of them will defend to their last breath the notion that the Christian God has absolutely nothing against homosexuality, when there is an overwhelming amount of Biblical evidence this belief is false.  The fallibility of humans is no excuse to invalidate the Bible, however.<br>
<br>
You may now continue with your regularly scheduled flamage. <p>Caledhon TelRana - 53 Warrior<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701">
Vethantis Soulbonker</a> - 57 Enchanter<br><b>Revolution</b>
